attributes.gcd: Refers to the field is used to map the payment system to a primary payment system, if such a linkage exists. A primary payment system, usually an RTGS-Real time gross settlement) system, is a central payment system, which is connected to other relatively smaller scale payment systems, through technical real time intraday liquidity bridges or other mechanisms. Intraday liquidity is considered fungible between the primary payment system and its linked systems. This field is only used if the payment system under consideration is not a primary payment system in itself. This is applicable only for Payment System Type as Large value payment systems(LVPS)
